The paper proposes a machine learning approach to playing poker, specifically using a CNN-based learning model. This suggests that the paper is likely to fall under the categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper deals with game theory and decision making, which could place it under the category of Game Theory (cs.GT). The use of a CNN model also suggests that the paper may fall under the category of Computer Vision (cs.CV), as this is a common application of CNNs. Finally, the paper discusses the use of iterative self-play and training, which could place it under the category of Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE).
